Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Technologist - English/Communication London , ON Description Technologist - English/Communication (LMS 41260) Library Learning Commons Student Services Location: London Employment Group: Support Hours:35 hours per week. Monday to Friday 8:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. Pay Details: $32.42 per hour Closing Date: February 9, 2024 Working at Fanshawe College Fanshawe College is committed to the principles of hybrid work and may offer this option to employees whose work can be performed in an alternate location, without adverse impact to the operations of the College, inclusive of our Student and Staff experience. Confirmation of hybrid work options available to you will be clarified upon hire and may be subject to change based on the duties required of your position. Successful candidates will be required to perform work within Ontario and must be available to work on campus, as required. Note: This is a full-time Support position (35 hours per week). Duties: Under the direction of the Director, the incumbent works as an integral part of the Learning Centre team to provide tutorial assistance to students. The incumbent prepares and delivers resource materials to provide students with opportunities to practice, apply and/or demonstrate the skills necessary to improve their writing and communication skills. Additionally, the incumbent provides general technical assistance to maintain relevant resources. QUALIFICATIONS Post-secondary 4-year degree Honours B.A. in English, Rhetoric and Composition, Linguistics or other related fieldMinimum 1-year related experience working in a tutorial or other educational settingAn equivalent combination of education and/or experience may be considered; preference will be given to applicants meeting the education requirementsExperience with second language learners an assetDemonstrated strong organizational skills and attention to detailDemonstrated ability to work independently and as a teamDemonstrated excellent verbal and written communication skills While transcripts are not required for the interview, they are mandatory prior to any offer of employment. How to Apply: For more information and how to apply, please visit the Fanshawe College website at:https://jobs.fanshawec.ca/ We thank all applicants for their interest; however, only those chosen for an interview will be acknowledged. Fanshawe College is an equal opportunity employer. We are committed to equity, value diversity, and welcome applicants from diverse backgrounds. Fanshawe College provides accommodations to job applicants with disabilities throughout the hiring process. If a job applicant requires an accommodation during the application process or through the selection process, the hiring manager and the Recruitment Coordinator leading the recruitment will work with the applicant to meet the job applicant's accommodation needs. Compensation Pay Details: $32.42 per hour Closes: 9 February, 2024 Fanshawe College London , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
