Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? University Librarian 24.11 Whitehorse , YT Description ABOUT THE OPPORTUNITY: YukonU invites you to consider joining the university as University Librarian, a new senior leadership role that will lead the northern-based, northern-focused university library at Canada’s first university north of sixty. ABOUT YOU AND YOUR ROLE: Joining a dedicated team of library staff and faculty, you will ensure the library evolves with the university through your oversight of the library’s services and resources, and through your own scholarly activity. Under your leadership, the YukonU library will provide high-quality library resources, learning opportunities and services to students, faculty and staff at all YukonU campuses in support of academic programming and research, including Indigenous-led research, pedagogy and data sovereignty. As an experienced, intuitive leader, you will inspire the sharing of information and knowledge, and you will connect YukonU to the broader community through the development of collaborative relationships with other libraries and archives, communities, governments and partners. Education and Experience Master’s in Library and Information Sciences (or equivalent) from an ALA-accredited programMinimum 5 years relevant experience, ideally with at least two years at a senior leadership level and experience in a post-secondary environmentSupervisory experience, ideally in a unionized environmentDemonstrated knowledge of library functions and service modelsDemonstrated knowledge of, and experience evaluating and implementing, new and emerging innovations, best practices and technologies relevant to library servicesDemonstrated experience championing information literacy through academic library resources and servicesExperience with resource management including budget responsibilityExperience with service-oriented delivery approachesProject management experience that includes ensuring delivery of high-quality results in the context of competing projects and tight deadlinesExperience with continuous improvement processes and process evaluationPrior experience developing and maintaining strong professional and personal relationships with diverse groups and individuals within and external to an organizationDemonstrated experience fostering diversity, equity and inclusion Aligned with Yukon University’s commitment to Reconciliation and pledge to employment equity, qualified applicants from Yukon First Nations may be given priority. Quoting the employment opportunity number, please include your cover letter, resume outlining your relevant experience and why you are interested in this position to hr@yukonu.ca. Compensation $63.27 to $79.09 per hour based on 75 hours bi-weekly. Permanant position starting April 1, 2024. Closes: 21 February, 2024 Yukon University Whitehorse , YT Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
