Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? St Albert Public Library: Programs Librarian and STARFest Director St. Albert , AB Description https://www.sapl.ca/about/job-and-volunteer-opportunities.htmlPROGRAMS LIBRARIAN and STARFest DIRECTORJoin us in building community in St. Albert and forging the future of public libraries in Alberta. We are looking for a dynamic leader with a love of writing, stories and reading, a passion for libraries, enthusiasm for community, people smarts and a head full of great ideas.We need a motivated person who wants to do interesting things from a public library platform. Want to build something great? We do too. We are looking for a person who can lead our efforts in programs for adults with a focus on reading, writing and literary programs and services, including our award-winning St. Albert Readers Festival (STARFest).Key ongoing and upcoming projects include the move from a single to a multiple location system with the Jensen Lakes Library launch, implementation of the Library’s 2023-2028 Strategic Plan: Here for YOU, Here for ALL and a robust post-pandemic return to in-person programs and events.You will be a key member of the Library’s Community Engagement team, working to implement library-wide initiatives and leading on literary initiatives. You have a passion for reading, writing and all things books. You value partnerships and collaboration as you will work with people outside the Library. You are a skilled people person, able to make the most of your colleagues and community members’ enthusiasm and expertise.Qualifications: MLS/MLIS or equivalent combination of relevant education and experience is preferred.Three years experience, preferably in a public library or related field.Successful track record of delivering innovative and engaging cultural programs or eventsWho we are:St. Albert Public Library is a vital part of the community, consistently rated as one of the key strengths of the city. It is a place where people learn, meet and share ideas, and enjoy leisure time. St. Albertans are avid readers and learners, and the Library has responded with excellent physical and digital collections, a unique place-based Summer Reading Game, and STARFest, an award-winning literary festival. Community is at the core of St. Albert Public Library, working to improve citizens’ lives through services focused on learning, leisure and community life.Where we are:St. Albert is a dynamic, beautiful and growing city of over 70,000 people, named the Best Place to Live in Canada. The main Library is located in downtown St. Albert on the banks of the Sturgeon River in St. Albert Place, an architectural jewel designed by Douglas Cardinal. One of Alberta’s oldest communities, St. Albert treasures its Francophone, First Nations and Métis heritage. Located on the northwest corner of Edmonton, St. Albert residents have the best of both worlds: a strong small-town sense of community with easy access to big city amenities.Job Description: View hereSalary band: $70,532.00 - $86,809.00 per annum.Hours of work: Permanent full-time position. 36 hours per week.Closing date: Sunday, February 11, 2024, at 5:00 p.m.To apply: Please email cover letter and resume to Stephanie Foremsky sforemsky@sapl.ca Compensation $70,532 - $86,809 Closes: 11 February, 2024 St. Albert Public Library St. Albert , AB Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
