Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Youth Services Librarian Cambridge , ON Description Posting #24-05x Youth Services LibrarianFull-Time, PermanentQueen's SquareIdea Exchange is a community hub comprised of the public libraries and art galleries for the City of Cambridge, a thriving city with a rich architectural heritage and the second largest community within the Waterloo Region. We are committed to supporting and inspiring our community in the exploration of reading, arts, innovation, and learning.Reporting to the Manager, Youth Services, the Youth Services Librarian supports the creation, planning, implementation, and evaluation of services addressing the needs of youth, teens, and families with school-aged children. The Youth Services Librarian will develop presentations for visits to local schools to engage students with Idea Exchange. The Youth Services Librarian will maintain Youth Services collections to meet the standards of Idea Exchange and is responsible for the development of reference and reader’s advisory services for youth ages 0-18.What You’ll DoAs Youth Services Librarian, you will:Support and provide expertise to Team Leads and staff in the development, delivery, and evaluation of youth programming.Work closely with local school teachers, librarians, students, and volunteers providing recreational, educational, and curricular materials both in the library and in the community.Evaluate materials, utilize statistical data and reports for collection maintenance, and make withdrawals according to library guidelines. Maintains the youth services collection at the Queen’s Square location and makes recommendations for Youth Services collections system-wide.Undertake system-wide projects, new initiatives and, large-scale events as project coordinator with an emphasis on Youth Services programming and collections. This includes research, recommendations, creation of training, piloting, evaluation and then final implementation to all locations.Conduct children’s and teen programs and assists with or conducts other programs or events as requested.Assist the Manager, Youth Services, in organizing the annual Children’s Summer Reading Club (SRC) for Idea Exchange. Participates in SRC Student grant writing, hiring and supervision, SRC committee work and evaluation of program.What You’ll Need to SucceedTo be qualified for and successful in the role, you should have:Required – University Masters in Library Information Science or Information StudiesRequired – Experience working in a public library –1 yearRequired – Experience working with youth in a work environment – 6 monthsRequired – Experience working in a service environment – 6 monthsAre highly-organized, and able to carry out job functions with flexibility, creativity and initiativeStrong analytical skills and a keen attention to detailExcellent multitasking skills and ability to complete responsibilities on timeExceptional verbal and written communication, critical thinking, and problem-solving skills, including the ability to explain complex technology to non-technical usersThe ability to connect with people of all ages and offer hands-on assistance.Demonstrated ability to collaborate professionally with internal and external partnersHas an inclusive and empathetic approach and a service-oriented mindsetA passion for supporting the diverse interests and needs of the Cambridge communityWhat We OfferWorking at Idea Exchange offers you the opportunity to be part of an organization that is welcoming, collaborative, and passionate about the community.We provide fair market compensation, excellent health, dental and vision benefits, consistent and reliable work schedules, paid sick time and free parking. We also offer participation in the OMERS pension plan.Pay: Salary range is $64,578 - $78,507 per year Hours: 70 hours in a two-week period.Schedule: Days, weekends and evenings may be required Week 1 Week 2 Monday 9:30am – 5:30pm OFF Tuesday 12:30pm – 8:30pm 12:30pm – 8:30pm Wednesday 9:30am - 5:30pm 9:30am – 5:30pm Thursday 9:30am – 5:30pm 9:30am – 5:30pm Friday 9:30am – 5:30pm 9:30am – 5:30pm Saturday 9:30am – 5:30pm OFF Sunday OFF OFF Note: schedules are service-driven and as such are subject to change.How to ApplyTo be considered for the position, please apply by February 1, 2024Tell us why we should consider you for this position! Please provide both a cover letter and resume, combined as a single PDF document.Submit your application by email to recruitment@ideaexchange.orgIf applying by email, please quote “24-05x Youth Services Librarian” in your email subject line.The anticipated start date for this position is February 2024.The position is open to internal and external candidates. We thank everyone for their interest, however only those candidates selected for an interview will be contacted.Additional InformationIdea Exchange aspires to employ a staff complement that fully represents the diversity of the community we serve. All qualified individuals who would contribute to the further diversification of our organization are encouraged to apply.Idea Exchange is an equal opportunity employer and is committed to accommodating individual needs in accordance with the Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act (AODA). If you require any accommodations at any point during the application and hiring process, please contact Human Resources at hr@ideaexchange.org.A Security Clearance Check with Vulnerable Sector Screening will be required. Compensation Salary range is $64,578 - $78,507 per year Closes: 1 February, 2024 Idea Exchange Cambridge , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
