Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Director, Public Service Caledon East , ON Description Caledon Public Library is a hub for discovery, innovation and inspiration. We nurture connections, collaboration and creativity and are situated within a quickly growing municipality that successfully balances urban, rural and agricultural communities. With seven branches that serve as the cornerstones to the community, connecting people to information and each other is what we do!We are seeking a dynamic, energetic and creative leader, who is passionate about public libraries, to be a part of our team. The OpportunityReporting directly to the CEO/Chief Librarian and as a member of the Senior Leadership Team, the Director of Public Service will champion an exemplary customer experience.The Director encourages all aspects of customer engagement and provides system-wide leadership in the delivery of public service in accordance with the policies and objectives of the Library Board. This position is responsible for the supervision of Public Service staff and facilities and in this capacity evaluates library services and initiates change to ensure that all staff and branches exemplify core library values. As the Director, Public Service, you will perform the following duties, including but not limited to: Providing strategic leadership in the area of innovative service development, ensuring that the library meets and exceeds established customer service objectives as defined in the strategic plan. Contributing to the development of strategic plans and the identification and implementation of annual project priorities and budgets in direct alignment with the Strategic Plan.Working in tandem with key stakeholders to support project management related to branch design, renovation and construction as a means of enhancing existing spaces and developing new locations. Administering the library budget related to branch and department operations and relevant capital projects; Determining budget requirements based on operational and staffing requirements of the library system.Recruiting, supporting, evaluating, and coaching direct reports (Branch Managers) Fostering and managing the Public Service department as a strategic partner within the organization, communicating department strategies clearly and effectively across the organization. Ensuring that the Integrated Library System is utilized to its full potential and in support of library policies and best practices. The Ideal CandidateWe are seeking an enthusiastic professional with a post-graduate degree in Library and Information Studies/Science, or an equivalent combination of education and experience. Our ideal candidate has a minimum of 7 years related experience in a public library setting, with a minimum of 4 years at a supervisory level.The ideal candidate will have a demonstrated ability to lead change and engage staff. We are seeking an individual with superior planning and project management skills, proven experience in ILS administration, and excellent communication skills.The successful candidate for Director, Public Service will be required to work a flexible schedule, including in the office, remotely and after hours (as required).This position offers a salary range of $105,256 - $128,993 (2023) plus a competitive benefit package.The full job description can be found at Job Description Director, Public Service.Satisfactory passing of a vulnerable sector check or criminal record check, and proof of qualifications will be required of any successful candidate(s) for this position. The Town and Library are committed to diversity and inclusivity in employment and welcomes applications from qualified individuals of diverse backgrounds. The Town and Library are equal opportunity employers that are committed to an inclusive and barrier-free workplace. If your application requires accommodation, please contact People Services at (905) 584-2272 Ext. 4738.Applications for this posting will be accepted until February 2, 2024, 4:30PM.How To ApplyTo learn more about employment with the Town of Caledon and to apply for this exciting and challenging opportunity, visit: www.caledon.ca/careersIf needed and upon request, this document can be made available in an alternative format. Compensation $105,256 - $128,993 Closes: 2 February, 2024 Town of Caledon Caledon East , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
