lopments in public library service, including trends related to technology, artificial intelligence, library as spaces for content creation, and community building.Experience working with diverse communities and developing services to meet a variety of needs.Excellent leadership and management skills, with ability to delegate and give clear direction diplomatically.Strong project management skills, with experience in managing multiple initiatives under time constraints.Strong communication skills, comfortable with writing reports or presenting to large groups.Ability to influence with diplomacy to advance organizational goals. Ability to research and analyse subject matter, identify issues and trends, and generate summaries and recommendations.Ability to think creatively, implement new ideas, and champion change.Ability to build and enhance effective working relationships with staff and external contacts. Salary: $139,842 – 159,630 How to apply If you are interested in this opportunity, send your cover letter and resume with the subject “Director, Public Services” to SPLEmployment@surrey.ca. The deadline is Monday, January 29, 2023. We thank in advance all applicants who apply and advise that only those selected for an interview will be contacted. Compensation $139,842 – 159,630 Closes: 29 January, 2024 Surrey Libraries Surrey , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
