unity networking and outreach techniques.- Plan, manage, and evaluate projects and programs from concept to completion, within budget and deadline; revise and adjust ongoing programs to meet library objectives; multitask and coordinate a variety of concurrent projects and activities.- Considerable knowledge of internet applications, social media, mobile devices, and office software.- Working knowledge of FOIP and the principles of intellectual freedom- Social media management, using office computer hardware and softwarePlease apply with a cover letter and resume to librarian@vplibrary.ca Accepting applications until the position is filled. Compensation This position is 21 hours per week and is eligible for a competitive health benefits package and pension plan with LAPP. The hourly salary grid range for this position is $21.32 to $24.94. Up to 30% remote work is available as minimum on site staffing req Closes: 15 February, 2024 Vermilion Public Library Vermilion , AB Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
